    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                
                <p>Your kind Letter came safe: I have little more to say than to beg the favor of you to make enquiry for my lodgings at my 
                    sisters<note type="editorial">Pennant refers to his twin sisters, <persName ref="pe0237">Catherine</persName> and 
                        <persName ref="pe0807">Sarah</persName> Pennant.</note> if I should not be able to call on you the 9<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 
                    of next month in the morning. Let me beg the favor of you to call on <persName ref="pe0026">white</persName> the Bookseller &amp; 
                    <sic>teise</sic> him to advertise my <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0045">Synopsis of Quadrupeds</title></bibl> as I have so often 
                    desired; &amp; to make him tell you has he done it. I set out on wednesday but shall be some days on the road by reason of calling at two places. 
                    I am Dear Sir</p>
                
              
                <closer><salute>Most truely y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>
                </salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">T Pennant</persName></signed></closer>
                <postscript><p><persName ref="pe2110">B. Williams</persName> &amp; I have <sic>shoke</sic> hands &amp; are good friends again.</p></postscript>
                
                
         
                
            </div>
            <div><p><stamp type="postmark">1 AP</stamp>
                <stamp type="handstamp"><placeName ref="pl0002">CHESTER</placeName></stamp></p>
            </div>
            
            <div>      
                <p><address><addrLine>To<lb/><persName ref="pe0803">John Lloyd esq<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.</persName> N<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>. 1.<lb/> 
                    <placeName ref="pl1344">Garden Court in the Temple</placeName> <lb/> <placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName>.
                    </addrLine></address></p>
            </div>
